   113	(pin-blocked atoms drain when passes end — R9), mints visStamps, notifies
   114	committed-world observers through its own path (I14), and clears every
   115	mask/bit/watermark it owns before slot recycle (I19). At quiescence,
   116	before K1 resets, every K1-touched node that committed state still watches
   117	is **refreshed** — K0-pulled at NEWEST so its true basis edges live in K0
   118	for the next episode (T8-N): the reach induction's premise is
   119	re-established at every episode boundary.
   120	
   121	**Numbers.** DIRECT = donor bytes ([ARENA]: at-or-below alien v3, tier-0,
   122	179/179); LOGGED-quiet floor measured 2.4–3.8% vs the ≤2% gate — pre-
   123	registered renegotiation (O19/SPK-L); carrier ≈0% unarmed, measured (I30).
   124	Everything else unmeasured is a spike (§16), never a claim.
   125	
   126	---
   127	
   128	## 2. Ground rules inherited (one paragraph each, binding)
   129	
   130	- **D1/I1 always-log**: LOGGED appends a receipt for every write; DIRECT
   131	  executes zero concurrency instructions. Activation monotonic (S6).
   132	- **D2 no drop-on-abort**: committed=false batches fold at retirement;
   133	  persistence never depends on subscription (S4).
   134	- **D3/I2 React's visibility/rebase semantics**: replay-in-write-order over
   135	  the pre-batch base; any mechanism must reproduce the seed math.
   136	- **D4 closed kernel**: no per-link world state in K0's hot walks; world
   137	  state lives in separate structures (tape, K1, columns).
   138	- **D5/D10/D13 delivery**: setState synchronously in the writer's context;
   139	  per-write; no implicit grouping; value-blind with per-(watcher, slot)
   140	  dedup only.
   141	- **D6 process apparatus inherited**: oracle-first, frozen-kernel contract
   142	  suite, bytecode budgets, pre-registered experiments, numeric exit gates.
   143	- **D7 co-designed fork**: protocol facts in §14; charter axes scored.
   144	- **D9 validity = clocks + epochs, no per-read certificates** (extended by
   145	  the closed change-source set, I16).
   146	- **D11 suspense key = fork lineage id** (+ content validity, I20/I24).
   147	- **D14/D15/D16**: fold reads throw in all builds; F8 = carrier + parking
   148	  with loud self-test; reducer staging + `ctx.previous` three-way rule +
   149	  lazy `ctx.use`.
   150	
   151	## 3. Concepts (plain English, before use)
   152	
   153	- **K0** — the canonical kernel: the donor arena (one Int32Array plane,
   154	  stride-8 interleaved node+link records, packed value side column,
   155	  premultiplied ids, DEPS_TAIL re-track cursor, iterative walks, split
   156	  link fast path). Holds every atom's NEWEST value and the newest-basis
   157	  topology. Closed and monomorphic (D4); CI bytecode budgets.
   158	- **DIRECT / LOGGED** — the twin engine builds. DIRECT = donor
   159	  byte-for-byte. LOGGED adds the guard, tape, routing, walks. One
   160	  generated source; op-table swap at `registerReactBridge()`.
   161	- **receipt / tape** — per-atom append-only log entry {op, slot, seq,
   162	  retiredSeq}. `op` is the set value or updater/reducer action. The tape
   163	  plus `base`/`baseSeq` (folded floor value and its max folded seq)
   164	  reconstruct any world's value.
   165	- **globalSeq** — the ONE monotone counter (I15). Mints write seqs, pins,
   166	  retirement stamps, visStamps, fnStamps, epochs.
   167	- **token / slot / mask** — a batch's fork-minted integer identity (F1),
   168	  never reused live; ≤31 live (I10) → interned to a 5-bit **slot**; a
   169	  world's included batches form a 32-bit **mask**. `slotWriteSeq[slot]`
   170	  (write clock, D9) bumps on every write in that slot.
   171	- **pin** — a pass's globalSeq snapshot; the pass sees no seq above it.
   172	- **world / worldKey** — an assignment of values to all atoms, defined by
   173	  (mask, pin, root-lock variant, episode epoch). **NEWEST** = K0's values.
   174	  **committed-for-root(r)** = retired ∪ locked-into-r (watermarked).
   175	  **RENDER_NEWEST** = a pass whose world currently equals NEWEST, served
   176	  from K0 directly; revocable (R3).
   177	- **lockedIn(root)** — per-root set of (slot, **watermark**) pairs; the
   178	  watermark is the pin of the pass whose commit locked that slot on that
   179	  root, advanced at each later commit of the slot there (R13/I25).
   180	- **visStamp(a)** — per-atom stamp minted from globalSeq at every
   181	  retirement fold touching `a` and at every per-root lock-in of a slot
   182	  holding entries of `a` (I21). Joins the fingerprint max.
   183	- **fingerprint** — `fp(atom, w) = max(newest w-visible entry seq,
   184	  baseSeq, reducerStamp, visStamp)`; the atom-grain validity fact.
   185	- **world memo** — `M(node, worldKey)` cached world evaluation with states
   186	  EMPTY/EVALUATING/DONE (EVALUATING read ⇒ R7 cycle throw).
   187	- **K1** — the second edge plane: REAL per-world dependency edges recorded
   188	  by world evaluations, union across worlds, add-only until quiescence;
   189	  record ids carry a 2-bit generation tag (wrap-clear).
   190	- **E-PRESERVE** — when a NEWEST re-track in K0 *removes* an edge while
   191	  any live receipts exist, the removed edge is mirrored into K1 so
   192	  committed/pinned-world reach survives the displacement (dev validator
   193	  SP2; mirrors are exempt from edge-add delivery — their paths already
   194	  existed and already flowed marks).
   195	- **touchedSlots(n)** — int32 cold column: bit k set ⇔ slot k's recorded
   196	  influence cone (K0∪K1, any time this episode) includes n (invariant M).
   197	  **touchedList[slot]** — per-slot append-only node-id list written on
   198	  0→1 transitions; the retainer sweep for clearing and targeting (I19).
   199	- **watcher** — a mounted hook's subscription record: node, component
   200	  setState, last-rendered value, per-slot dedup bits (re-armed on render).
   201	- **staged evaluator** — per-pass table hookNode → {fn, deps, fnStamp}
   202	  (+ staged reducer); consulted only by that pass's evaluations; promoted
   203	  at the hook's own commit effect; dies with the pass (I22). The
   204	  **committed evaluator** is the last promoted one.
   205	- **flattened prefix** — for a suspense position: the ordered transitive
   206	  [(atomId, fp(atom, w))…] of tracked reads plus [(computedId,
   207	  effectiveFnStamp)] of evaluators traversed before the position; child
   208	  evaluations merge into parents (S5's flatten rule).
   209	- **pass / lineage / episode** — pass: one render attempt, spanning
   210	  yields (F2, per-callstack truth — I6). Lineage: fork-minted id per
   211	  (root × batch-set), stable across restarts/replays, dead at
   212	  commit/abandon (F5, D11). Episode: bridge-registration or quiescence to
   213	  the next quiescence; epoch-bumped.
   214	- **staging (S15)** — arena records minted during a pass live on a
   215	  staging list until their hook's commit effect promotes them;
   216	  pass/lineage death reclaims unpromoted records (no arena leak).
   217	- **fold frame / world-eval frame / pass binding** — the three restricted
   218	  frames the write guard rejects (R12/R4/render-purity).
   219	- **carrier** — the async-action token continuation carrier: module
   220	  variable `currentToken`; captured at async-resource creation, pushed
   221	  before each continuation, finally-restored (I26). Realized by the
   222	  **twin-build async transform** (§12) or platform AsyncContext.
   223	- **CT(n)** — "committed-clean": for a computed, K0 holds a cached value
   224	  the donor pull would return without re-evaluating; for an atom, the
   225	  tape is empty. The freshness half of invariant R.
   226	
   227	## 4. Mode protocol
   228	
   229	Twin generated builds from one source (SPK-H/SPK-Q both TRIGGERED — the
   230	hooks and routing cost >1%/>2% if compiled into DIRECT; the remedy is
   231	structural, not a flag). `registerReactBridge()` swaps the op-table once;
   232	the plane, values, and topology carry over; no state migration. LOGGED
   233	mode is permanent for the process (monotonic — S6's first-transition-leak
   234	schedule is unrepresentable: the bridge exists before any React write can
   235	happen, because writes classify through fork facts that only exist after
   236	registration). LOGGED-quiet residual: measured 2.4–3.8% branch floor
   237	[SPKHQ]; gate G-Q AT RISK with the pre-registered renegotiation (O19,
   238	SPK-L; mitigation ladder = fused status load, per-pass routing hoist).
   239	DIRECT-mode users get donor bytes: G-D's CI symbol check diffs the DIRECT
   240	bundle against the donor per commit.
   241	
   242	## 5. Value model
   243	
   244	### 5.1 The logged write path
   245	
   246	```
   247	write(atom, op):
   248	  if restrictedFrame(): throw            // pass binding | world-eval frame | fold frame — FIRST, before any mutation
   249	  if liveRenderNewestCount > 0: demoteRenderNewestPasses()   // R3: flip to real (mask, pin); original pins retained
   250	  token = fork.currentBatchToken()       // carrier-aware (§12); lazy mint; microtask backfill (F1)
   251	  slot  = internSlot(token)              // zeroes slotWriteSeq at first intern
   252	  seq   = ++globalSeq;  slotWriteSeq[slot] = seq
   253	  if atom.tape.length == 0: atom.base = k0.value(atom); atom.baseSeq = 0
   254	  atom.tape.push({op, slot, seq, retiredSeq: 0})   // ALWAYS (I1/I7/C8) — equal values included
   255	  k0.writeNewest(atom, applyStable(op, k0.value(atom)))   // stepwise equality: keep old ref, skip K0 marks only
   256	  notifyWalk(atom, slot)                 // unconditional; value-blind (D13)
   257	```
   258	
   259	`update(fn)` and reducer application run under a **fold frame**: signal
   260	reads and writes inside throw in ALL builds, even through `untracked`
   261	(R12/I28/D14; legal composition = read before dispatch; conformance-
   262	pinned). Equal-value writes still append receipts: with any history,
   263	worlds disagree about the accumulator (I7); with no history the write may
   264	be short-circuited after one evaluation against base (the only legal
   265	drop).
   266	
   267	### 5.2 Folds: equality-stable replay + watermarked visibility
   268	
   269	`foldAtom(atom, w)`: `acc = base`; for each visible entry in seq order:
   270	`next = apply(op, acc); acc = atom.isEqual(acc, next) ? acc : next`
   271	(R15/I29 — reference stability identical to the live K0 write path).
   272	ReducerAtom rides the same tape; the fold uses the committed reducer
   273	except inside a pass holding a staged one (I22/D16).
   274	
   275	Visibility of entry e for world w = (mask M from F2, root r, pin p):
   276	
   277	```
   278	  (e.retiredSeq ≠ 0 ∧ e.retiredSeq ≤ p)                       // retired clause — unconditional (I15: same number line)
   279	∨ (e.slot ∈ M ∧ e.seq ≤ p)                                    // pass's own tokens — plain clause (mask parity)
   280	∨ (e.slot ∈ L(r) ∧ e.seq ≤ min(p, lockedSeq[r][e.slot]))      // locked tokens — WATERMARKED (R13/I25)
   281	```
   282	
   283	For synchronous batches every write predates the first commit, so the
   284	watermark equals the full clause; only carrier-attributed post-await
   285	writes exercise the bound (walk C11-W). Both pins sit on the globalSeq
   286	line (I15) — a private retire counter is unrepresentable here.
   287	
   288	### 5.3 Retirement (fold; exactly once per token — F3)
   289	
   290	1. Stamp every entry of the token `retiredSeq = ++globalSeq`; mint
   291	   `worldMemoEpoch = ++globalSeq` (R10).
   292	2. Per touched atom (enumerated via touchedList[slot]): fold the
   293	   compactable **all-retired prefix only** — blocked at the first
   294	   unretired entry (CH-4's 3-not-4 fold is unrepresentable) and blocked
   295	   below any live pass pin (C7 retention); `baseSeq = max(baseSeq, max
   296	   folded seq)`; **mint visStamp(atom)** (R1/I21). Pin-blocked atoms go on
   297	   the pending-compaction list (R9).
   298	3. Run the retirement notification path — the **plain full walk** from
   299	   each touched atom whose committed value moved (no pruning exists to
   300	   consult — CH-7), the reconcile backstop (§11.3), and the per-root
   301	   targeted effect flush (§11.4) — I14's three triggers.
   302	4. Clear bit(slot) + watermark from every root's lockedIn **before** slot
   303	   release; recycle zeroes slotWriteSeq, dedup columns, touched bits via
   304	   touchedList[slot] (I19).
   305	5. Ordering (R11): steps 1–4's per-root bookkeeping (lock-in watermark,
   306	   fold when this commit retires the token) complete **before that root's
   307	   layout effects run** — fork F3 clause, fork test 16.
   308	
   309	`onPassEnd`/lineage death advance min-live-pin and drain the
   310	pending-compaction list, then re-check quiescence (R9 — a pass-held pin
   311	can never permanently strand compaction, HX-7).
   312	
   313	### 5.4 Quiescence (episode boundary)
   314	
   315	Precondition: live batches = 0, live passes = 0, tapes compacted
   316	(reachable by R9). Then, **before** K1 reset:
   317	
   318	- **Refresh (T8-N).** For every K1-touched node with a committed watcher
   319	  or an effect-dep snapshot (scope includes effect deps — LC-F6), K0-pull
   320	  at NEWEST — legal (no worlds exist), re-tracks the node's true basis
   321	  into K0; donor recursion fixes stale upstream. Why: the reach induction
   322	  (§6.4) presumes basis edges present; a node whose current basis exists
   323	  only in K1 would strand when K1 clears — next episode's write to its
   324	  real dep reaches nothing → torn commit. The refresh restores the
   325	  premise at every boundary. If a refresh pull performs an R8-legal
   326	  computed write, quiescence has ended: finish the sweep, retry once at
   327	  the next quiescence; a node that writes again is **refresh-exempt** —
   328	  its K1 in-edges are carried into the fresh plane (over-notification
   329	  only, bounded by the exempt cone, dev-warned; LC-F3's livelock closed).
   330	- Then: bump episodeEpoch (K1 tag wrap-clear duty at tag wrap), bump-reset
   331	  K1, zero touchedSlots + lists, drop worldKeys/memos (epoch-in-key makes
   332	  stragglers unreachable), staging reclamation sweep, optional globalSeq
   333	  renumber past the quiescent margin (§15.2).
   334	
   335	## 6. Worlds, routing, marks
   336	
   337	### 6.1 World bindings
   338	
   339	Reads outside any pass binding resolve NEWEST (K0). Pass bindings come
   340	from F2 — (mask, pin, lineage, root) — pushed at pass start/resume and
   341	popped at yield/end (**per-callstack truth**, I6: handlers in yield gaps
   342	are outside the binding — S7's wall-clock scoping is unrepresentable).
   343	Effects and fixups bind committed-for-root(r). RENDER_NEWEST: a pass
   344	whose visible set covers every live receipt at pass start (conservative
   345	test: every live slot ∈ mask ∪ locked(r), every live seq ≤ pin, no
   346	watermark bound below a live seq — or simply zero live receipts) binds
   347	K0 directly; **revocable**: the first logged write while any
   348	RENDER_NEWEST binding is live demotes those bindings to their real
   349	(mask, pin) worlds, original pins retained (R3; walk C7-D).
   350	
   351	### 6.2 Read routing (invariant R)
   352	
   353	A tracked or untracked read of node n under world w ≠ NEWEST:
   354	
   355	```
   356	if touchedSlots(n) == 0 and CT(n):  serve K0's cached value   // fast path
   357	else:                                world path
   358	```
   359	
   360	World path: atoms fold (§5.2); computeds consult `M(n, worldKey)` —
   361	EMPTY → evaluate under a **world-eval frame** (write guard rejects writes
   362	inside it — R4), reading deps recursively under w, recording every read
   363	as a K1 edge, storing DONE + value + validity record; EVALUATING → R7
   364	cycle throw; DONE → validity ladder (§8.2), serve or re-evaluate.
   365	
   366	**Invariant R (the routing soundness claim), with its construction.**
   367	Claim: the fast path never serves a value that world w's own evaluation
   368	would not produce. Construction: worlds diverge from NEWEST only through
   369	receipts (folds differ from K0 only in visible entries; base is shared).
   370	Suppose w's value of n differs from K0's cache. By first-divergence (I4):
   371	n's w-evaluation and NEWEST evaluation read identical prefixes up to the
   372	first atom x whose w-value ≠ newest value; x necessarily holds a live
   373	receipt in some slot s, and x is a dependency of n *on the newest basis
   374	at that point*. Then bit s reached n through one of exactly three legs:
   375	(leg 1) the write walk from x over K0∪K1 at the time of x's write, if a
   376	path existed then; (leg 2) edge-add propagation (§6.4 site 3), if the
   377	path was created later by any evaluation; (leg 3) E-PRESERVE, if a K0
   378	re-track displaced the path while receipts lived (the mirror keeps it
   379	walkable). So touchedSlots(n) ∋ s ≠ 0 — the fast path refused. The
   380	**freshness conjunct CT(n)** (I12) closes the remaining hole (S9): if
   381	K0's cache needed a recompute, serving would trigger a *fresh
   382	newest-basis evaluation* that can acquire a receipted atom through an
   383	edge no plane recorded *before the pull itself creates it* — legs 1–3
   384	cover recorded paths only, so only cached, no-recompute serves are legal.
   385	Base case: episode start — no receipts, all worlds ≡ NEWEST, any serve
   386	correct. Step: every event kind preserves the M-invariant (§6.4
   387	induction). ∎
   388	
   389	### 6.3 Invariant M: per-slot marks with delivering propagation
   390	
   391	**M:** if atom x has a live-episode receipt in slot k and a path x→…→n
   392	exists in K0∪K1 **at any time while the bit is live**, then
   393	`touchedSlots(n) ∋ k`.
   394	
   395	Maintenance sites (the induction over event kinds):
   396	
   397	1. **Write walk** — ORs the writing slot's bit into every visited node
   398	   (0→1 appends to touchedList[slot]).
   399	2. **World evaluation** — ORs the union of its deps' bits into the
   400	   evaluated node (covers paths traversed by evaluation order).

