   427	## 7. K1 (the world edge plane)
   428	
   429	Same-plane layout class as K0's links (I9: interleaving, closure-bound
   430	buffer, bump allocation); separate plane so K0's walks stay closed (D4).
   431	Populated only by world evaluations (each records its REAL read set) and
   432	by E-PRESERVE mirrors. Union across worlds, add-only to quiescence —
   433	over-notification is priced (G3), never wrongness (delivery is
   434	value-blind; React bails out on equal renders). Record ids carry a 2-bit
   435	generation tag; quiescence bump-resets the plane and bumps the tag; a
   436	retained id from a prior episode fails its tag check; every fourth
   437	episode (tag wrap) runs the full clear sweep of retained-id columns
   438	(CH-8's enumeration hole does not apply to tags). Memory ~128 KiB warm,
   439	reused. Dev-mode E-PRESERVE validator (SP2): brute-force compare
   440	committed-world evals against a shadow graph; >10% dev overhead → sampled
   441	validation (O3).
