   805	## 14. fork-protocol (versioned document; the seam)
   806	
   807	Eight facts; ~12 reconciler touch sites; integers and callbacks only (no
   808	Fiber, no lane bitmask, no queue internals cross the boundary). Bindings
   809	feature-detect via F7 and fail loudly on stock React.
   810	
   811	- **F1 — write classification.** `currentBatchToken()`: the carrier's
   812	  token if non-null (§12), else the current event/update context's token
   813	  — minted lazily `(serial<<1)|deferredBit`, never reused live, ≤31 live
   814	  (I10); microtask backfill finalizes lane assignment for tokens claimed
   815	  before React scheduled. Transitions multiplexed onto one lane share one
   816	  token (parity by construction). Sites: dispatch entry, transition
   817	  scope, registry mint/backfill.
   818	- **F2 — pass lifecycle.** `onPassStart(root, mask, pin, lineageId)` /
   819	  `onPassYield` / `onPassResume` / `onPassEnd(complete|discard)` —
   820	  per-callstack truth (I6): the binding pops at yield, re-pushes at
   821	  resume; handlers in gaps are outside it. Invariant: mask == the lane
   822	  set React renders (mask parity — the plain visibility clause depends
   823	  on it). Sites: workLoop entry/exit, shouldYield boundary.
   824	- **F3 — retirement + lock-in + parking.** Exactly once per token, with
   825	  committed flag; `onBatchCommittedOnRoot(token, rootId, passPin)` per
   826	  root (watermark data — R13); **ordering clause (R11): per-root lock-in
   827	  bookkeeping and, when the last root commits, the retirement fold
   828	  complete before that root's layout effects run**; async actions park
   829	  retirement until the returned thenable settles (React's entangled-
   830	  action settlement is the trigger). Sites: commitRoot, action-settle.
   831	- **F4 — `runInBatch(token, cb)`.** cb's updates join token's lanes.
   832	  **Obligation:** an update scheduled into a completed-not-committed
   833	  pass's lanes schedules further work for those lanes — never silently
   834	  absorbed into the finished tree (C10-R's post-completion window).
   835	  Retired token ⇒ documented error return (caller falls back per §11.2).
   836	  Site: priority-override scope.
   837	- **F5 — lineage.** `lineageId` per (root × batch-set): minted at first
   838	  pass for the set, stable across restarts/replays/yields, dead at
   839	  commit/abandon (D11). Site: root render session.
   840	- **F6 — mutation window.** Brackets around the commit mutation phase
   841	  (kept per charter). Site: commit mutation phase.
   842	- **F7 — handshake.** Protocol version export + capability record
   843	  (includes carrier rung, §12.3); mismatch/absence ⇒ loud failure.
   844	- **F8 — action scope.** Enter/exit + the continuation carrier contract
   845	  (§12): scope entry publishes the token to the carrier; the fork
   846	  guarantees parking; the **build layer** guarantees continuation
   847	  identity (rung 2) or the host does (rung 1). The self-test (§12.4) is
   848	  part of this fact's conformance.
   849	
   850	**Rebase drill** ("React changed X — what moves?"): the library moves
   851	zero lines in every drill; the fork re-implements the fact and its test
   852	is the tripwire. Lanes renamed/renumbered ⇒ F1/F2's token↔lane registry
   853	only (tests 1–2). Commit phases reordered ⇒ F3's ordering clause
   854	re-anchors (test 16). Update-queue internals rewritten ⇒ nothing (no
   855	queue internals cross the seam). Async-action internals changed ⇒ F8
   856	parking re-anchors at the new settle edge (test 13); the carrier is
   857	build-side and does not move. Scheduler yield mechanics changed ⇒ F2's
   858	yield/resume edges re-anchor (test 5).
   859	
   860	**Fork test list (reconciler-level, run on every rebase):**
   861	1 token mint/classify per update kind; 2 mask parity (pass include-set ==
   862	React's lane decision, incl. flushSync exclusion); 3 retirement
   863	exactly-once + committed flag; 4 async parking (close vs settle); 5
   864	yield/resume edges (handler in gap sees no binding); 6 runInBatch joins
   865	live lanes; 7 runInBatch on retired token errors; 8 lineage stable across
   866	restart/replay; 9 lineage dead at commit/abandon; 10 mutation-window
   867	brackets; 11 handshake + stock-React loud failure; 12 flushSync excludes
   868	pending default batch (C2 shape); 13 action parking differential vs
   869	React 19 (React-state side); 14 queued edge-add deliveries drain at
   870	yield/end in token order; 15 per-root lock-in event carries (token,
   871	rootId, passPin); 16 lock-in/retirement-fold precede that root's layout
   872	effects (R11); 17 watermark equals the committed pass's pin (C11-W
   873	schedule); 18 carrier matrix (native await, timers, clicks between
   874	continuations, interleaved actions, ambient-null restore); **19 (new)
   875	build self-test: missing-transform boot throw; probe-pass path;
   876	uncompiled-boundary dev-warn fires on token-null write during parked
   877	action and names the vendor remedy**.
