   129	The trap either way: any *implicit* grouping (e.g. coalescing broadcasts per
   130	event without user-visible `batch()`) cannot be forbidden — the user wrote
   131	no special code — so implicit grouping must preserve per-write context or
   132	not exist. State which your design does.
   133	
   134	## C7 — Writes and reads during a yielded render pass
   135	
   136	Schedule: a transition render is time-sliced and yields; during the yield a
   137	click handler runs: reads `a.state`, writes `a.set(x)`; the pass later
   138	resumes.
